  "text": "We next investigated the mechanism determining the sorting of NRP-1 to Rab11 vesicles. NRP-1 associates with a cytoplasmic Figure 1D ) whereas the individual receptors were found in Rab4 and Rab11 vesicles, respectively ( Figure 1C , quantified in Figure 1E-F [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] The last 3 amino acids of NRP-1, SEA, are required for PDZ domain-mediated GIPC binding. [CITATION_3] To test the influence of the GIPC binding motif on NRP-1 and VEGFR-2 localization, we expressed wild-type and a mutant NRP-1 (NRP-1-S921X) lacking the last 3 amino acids in PAECs stably expressing VEGFR-2. Both NRP-1 variants accumulated at the plasma membrane in unstimulated cells ( Figure 4A-B) . NRP-1 was cleared from the plasma membrane after VEGF stimulation and transferred to vesicles within 30 minutes (Figure 4C-D) . Wild-type NRP-1 reappeared on the plasma membrane 180 minutes after stimulation with VEGF-A 165 a ( Figure 4E ), whereas NRP-1-S921X remained associated with intracellular vesicles ( Figure 4F , quantified in Figure 4G ). NRP-1-S921X was predominantly found in Rab5, ",
